<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-683-519  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 683 519.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 30 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI announces new audio conferencing services. (MCI CommunicationsCorp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (Services).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     Telephone companiesTeleconferencingCustomer RelationsMCI Forum.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MCI ANNOUNCES NEW AUDIO CONFERENCING SERVICES 11/30/90 WASHINGTON, D.C.,andO;U.S.A., 1990 NOV 30 (NB) -- MCI has followed ATandamp;T and Sprint into thelong-distance teleconferencing business with a service called MCI Forum.andP;  Itsmost unique aspect is the use of toll-free 800 numbers and a promise callerswill wait on hold no more than 10 minutes before a conference call begins.andM;The conferencing market looks more important to MCI and others during thecurrent recession because telephone conferences can reduce the need forexpensive trips and face-to-face meetings, according to C. Thomas Faulders,senior vice president of MCI Enterprise Group.andP;  Telephone conferences canalso be set up quickly.andP;  &quot;Analysts say it's appropriate during the downturn,&quot;an MCI spokesman told Newsbytes.andM;The two unique features of MCI Forum are called Personal 800 Meet Me and ASAPCalling.andP;  Personal 800 Meet Me allows the customer to use the same 800 numberfor all conference calls.andP;  At the time of a meeting, those attending simplydial a corporate 800-number and start talking.andP;  This simplifies billing.andO;ASAP Calling allows meeting organizers to send MCI Forum conference operatorsmeeting requests by phone or fax, without a prior reservation.andP;  The operatorsthen bring participants together as quickly as possible, usually within 10minutes, said the spokesman.andM;Customers wanting to use MCI Forum simply call a special 800 number forassistance.andP;  MCI Forum also features Dial-Out Calling, where the operatorcalls each conference participant at a prereserved time and connects him orher to the conference.andP;  Canadian and international locations, as well asdomestic sites, can be included in Dial-Out calls.andP;  The charge for Dial-OutCalling is 35 cents per minute and $6 per participant location for domesticcalls.andP;  Cost for Personal 800 Meet Me is 45 cents per minute and $6 perparticipant location for domestic calls, plus a one-time setup charge of $35.andO;Cost for ASAP depends on the call- type chosen, either Dial-Out or Personal800 Meet Me, and is priced accordingly.andP;  MCI Forum can handle 3,000 people ona call, making it ideal for broadcasts of press conferences.andM;MCI Forum is available 24 hours a day, seven days a week, and you can get iteven if you're not a regular MCI customer by dialing 1-800-475-4700.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19901130/Press Contact: MCI, John Houser, 1- 800-289-0073)</TEXT></DOC>